properties.areaDesc: San Diego County Deserts; Coachella Valley; San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning; Apple and Lucerne Valleys
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 1:22PM PST until February 3 at 12:00PM PST by NWS San Diego CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
expected.

* WHERE...Apple and Lucerne Valleys, Coachella Valley, San Diego
County Deserts and San Gorgonio Pass Near Banning. Strongest
winds will be near the foothills and through San Gorgonio Pass.

* WHEN...From 4 PM Sunday to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Power outages are possible. Travel will be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds. Use caution while driving.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM SUNDAY TO NOON PST MONDAY
